# BriefingIQ JMeter Runner

Data-population runner (not load testing): Node API + Angular UI execute JMeter plans against BriefingIQ.

## Layout

- `plans/*.jmx` — **active test plans** (primary: `plans/BIQ.jmx`)
- `BIQ.jmx` (repo root) — legacy; do not edit unless explicitly asked
- `server.js` + `jmx-parameters.js` — API, parsing, field-options proxy
- `ui/` — Angular 21 SPA
- `runs/` — gitignored run artifacts; analyze logs there when debugging runs

## Dev commands

```bash
npm run init    # first-time setup
npm run validate # prerequisite check only
npm run dev     # API :5050 + UI :4200
```

## Change discipline

- Minimize scope; match existing patterns in the file you touch
- Do not commit `runs/`, `.env`, or Bearer tokens
- Do not create git commits or PRs unless the user asks
- README is the source of truth for prerequisites (Node 20.19+, JMeter 5.4+, jpgc-json plugin)

## Debugging runs

When the user gives a run ID, inspect `runs/<id>__<label>/jmeter.log`, `result.jtl`, and `run.meta.json` before guessing.
